{"questionId":"2607442","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The base of a right cone lies in&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Π</mi></math> centred at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math> such that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> is a tangent to its base. The volume of the cone is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>90</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math> cubic units.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the two possible positions of the vertex of the cone.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>substituting their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> into volume formula and equating&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi>π</mi><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><msqrt><mn>6</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>90</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mi>π</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math> (seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>recognition that the position vector of vertex is given by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mrow><mi>O</mi><mtext>A</mtext></mrow><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mi>μ</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">n</mi></math> OR <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>OA</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mi>h</mi><mo>×</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">n</mi><mo mathvariant=\"bold\">^</mo></mover></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>6</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>8</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>μ</mi><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>μ</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>μ</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>μ</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>recognition that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>μ</mi><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">n</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>h</mi></math> (where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>μ</mi></math> is a parameter)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>μ</mi><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">n</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math> OR<em> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><msup><mi>μ</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>μ</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>μ</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;</em>OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>μ</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>75</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mo>⇒</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mi>μ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>μ</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>±</mo><mn>5</mn></math> (accept <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>μ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn></math>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to find cone’s height vector <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>×</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">n</mi><mo mathvariant=\"bold\">^</mo></mover></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">n</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mfrac><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mfrac><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>6</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>8</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>±</mo><mn>5</mn><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>6</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>8</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>±</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>5</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>vertex = <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>11</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo></math> and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>13</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo></math> (accept position vectors)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;Award a maximum of&nbsp;<em><strong>(M0)A0(M1)(M1)(A1)A1A1FT</strong></em>&nbsp;for</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>39</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mfrac><mn>17</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mfrac><mn>47</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mfrac><mn>27</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;obtained using&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mover><mi>PA</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mfenced></math>&nbsp;from part (c).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[7 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"2607442","referenceCode":"23M.1.AHL.TZ1.12e","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the two possible positions of the vertex of the cone.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"e","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 7]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.1—3d space, volume, angles, distance, midpoints","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.16—Vector product"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}